h3. Summary
Clicking on the help dropdown menu (top right) and clicking on JIRA Software help takes the user to a broken link.
 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Click on help > JIRA Software help
# Web-browser opens

h3. Expected Results
The web link should take the user to the JIRA Software documentation
h3. Actual Results
The web link takes the user to the following link https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/$%7Bsoftware.help.space%7D/ instead
 
h3. Workaround #1
# Navigate manually to https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRASOFTWARESERVER072

h3. Workaround #2
# Add in "Announcement Banner".

Customer must be aware that if he does so then "JIRA Software Help" will be hidden at all places in your JIRA instance. Moreover, even if he upgrades/downloads, restart his instance, this announcement banner is going to behave same. He needs to remember to unhide it manually.

(i) If that is ok for him this is the code for the AB:

{code:java}
<style>
div#system-help-menu-content a#gh_view_help {display:none !important }
</style>
{code}

h3. Workaround #3

Add it to your Announcement Banner at *Administration > System > Announcement banner (under User Interface)*: 
{code:html}
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
	var helpLink = $("a#gh_view_help.aui-nav-link"); 
	helpLink.attr("href", "https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/jsw-docs-084/"); 
});
</script>
{code} 
The above will replace the link with the right URL. 
(i) Example above is for JIRA Software 8.4 documentation.

It seems that for the 7.2 there were changes made to Project Panel - > Report generation. The changes seems to be working the first time the reports are generated for multiselect, however it seems that when the user clicks on Configure again after the reports are generated, the below section of code is trying to cast a String[] to a String resulting in a failure. This is a very important feature for us and is breaking key functionality for us. 

To reproduce this error, do the following

1. create a plugin with a report having multiselect
2. go to the Project and click on the report, generate the report selecting multiple values.
3. Once the  report is generated, click on the Configure field again. This results in the Classcast exception. This happens for multiselect (single select works fine due to the casting in the class).

Class throwing Error: com.atlassian.jira.plugin.corereports.web.action.ConfigureReport.ObjectConfigurationField
 
{code:java}
// The below method is defined in the ObjectConfigurationField class which is an inner class of ConfigureReport. This method makes a call to getParamValue which assumes that request params are of type String which is not correct for multiselect.

      public String getParamValue() {
            return ConfigureReport.this.getParamValue(fieldKey);
        }
{code}

  
Reason: 
   The above method makes a call to getParamValue which tries to cast a String[] to String. The right method to involve is either ConfigureReport.this.getParamValues(fieldKey);

Basically, there is few fault behaviour when  try to use Perforce Job Integration (bundled with Fisheye plugin in *JIRA 6.0.2*)

h3. Steps to reproduce:
# Fresh install JIRA 6 and connect it with Fisheye 3.0.2
# Install Perforce and configure it all the necessary connectioon
# Then set-up the Perforce Job Integration in (Administration > Add-ons)

h3. The following is the fault behaviour after you successfully connect JIRA with Perforce:
# Editing p4 configuration [^1.jpg] leads to new p4 integration creation [^2.jpg](whereby the exisiting value of the configuration will be missing).
# Test connection doesn't do anything [^3.jpg] (when click either one of the link it doesn't show anything, basically the page will just refresh itself and there is no changes at all)
# It is not possible to select perforce config under project config. It always select the option *none*. [^4.jpg]
# Unable to delete configurations created in the first step [^5.jpg] (it will show the stack traces in the screenshot)


(i) *Side Note:* I have done further testing and all of these is working absolutely fine for the Perforce Job Integration in JIRA 4.4 and JIRA 5.2.11

h3. Workaround to delete Perforce configuration
(!) Please note this procedure will make changes directly in your database. Please make sure you take a backup before applying this procedure
# Shutdown JIRA.
# Run the following SQL queries in your database:
{code:sql}delete from propertydata where id in (select id from propertyentry where property_key like 'fisheye.p4%');
delete from propertydate where id in (select id from propertyentry where property_key like 'fisheye.p4%');
delete from propertydecimal where id in (select id from propertyentry where property_key like 'fisheye.p4%');
delete from propertynumber where id in (select id from propertyentry where property_key like 'fisheye.p4%');
delete from propertystring where id in (select id from propertyentry where property_key like 'fisheye.p4%');
delete from propertytext where id in (select id from propertyentry where property_key like 'fisheye.p4%');
delete from propertyentry where property_key like 'fisheye.p4%';{code}
# Start JIRA.

